Mather Brown: Early American Artist in England
Wesleyan University Press | 1982 | ISBN 0819559698 | Eng | 334 pages | PDF | 41.4 MB

Of the major early American artists, painter and portraitist Mather Brown (1761-1831) is the least known. The first full-length study of his life and work, Mather Brouni: Early American Artist iji England brings attention to the high quality of his work and elucidates the apparent contradiction between his considerable popularity during his lifetime and his subsequent obscurity in the history of American art
